WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.091
.

00:04.134 --> 00:06.528
- I stand by
my original statement.

00:06.571 --> 00:09.661
Officer Doyle
had no probable cause.

00:09.705 --> 00:13.230
- Atwater snitched
on the police.

00:13.274 --> 00:15.928
- Every time I see a cop,
I get nervous.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.321
- He's gotta pay the price.

00:17.365 --> 00:19.845
[siren wails]
- Blue Wall is a tricky thing.

00:19.889 --> 00:23.153
- Step out of the vehicle.
- Look, I'm police.

00:23.197 --> 00:25.068
Is this really
what you want to do?

00:25.112 --> 00:26.939
Black man?

00:26.983 --> 00:28.985
- It's gotta stop now
before someone gets hurt.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.074
[all grunting]

00:31.118 --> 00:32.554
- [grunts]

00:32.597 --> 00:33.859
[panting]

00:33.903 --> 00:36.993
[drill whirring]

00:37.037 --> 00:40.127
[door opens]

00:42.433 --> 00:45.175
- You--you kidding me?
You know it's 6:00 a.m.?

00:45.219 --> 00:47.264
- Yeah, I got work
in the field.

00:47.308 --> 00:49.658
- What even is all this?

00:49.701 --> 00:51.094
- A new security system.

00:51.138 --> 00:52.835
Cameras on every door,

00:52.878 --> 00:55.055
sensors all over the house.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.360
- Right.
What?

00:56.404 --> 00:57.709
Maybe the beatdown
was the end of it?

00:57.753 --> 01:00.669
- Or the beginning.
- Look, bro, come on.

01:00.712 --> 01:03.324
Maybe the white cops
will finally realize

01:03.367 --> 01:05.065
that they're the racist pricks

01:05.108 --> 01:06.544
on the wrong end
of a revolution.

01:06.588 --> 01:08.198
- Revolutions ain't ever
that fast, Jordan.

01:08.242 --> 01:10.548
[car horn honks]

01:10.592 --> 01:12.985
I'm not gonna be
driving my car so much.

01:13.029 --> 01:15.292
- What else do you think
they're gonna do to your car?

01:15.336 --> 01:17.555
- If anybody's here that
shouldn't be, you let me know.

01:17.599 --> 01:20.689
Clean this up,
all right?

01:22.865 --> 01:25.824
[tense music]

01:25.868 --> 01:32.788
♪

01:42.145 --> 01:44.408
[blowing]

01:46.018 --> 01:47.759
[radio whirs]

01:47.803 --> 01:50.806
[radio static]

02:07.170 --> 02:08.954
- You good, Kev?

02:08.998 --> 02:10.478
- Yeah...

02:10.521 --> 02:13.698
I think they locked me out.
- Meaning?

02:13.742 --> 02:16.048
- The system's
not letting me in.

02:16.092 --> 02:18.312
My radio doesn't work.

02:18.355 --> 02:20.705
I don't have any access.

02:20.749 --> 02:22.751
- What happened?

02:25.319 --> 02:27.930
- They jumped me.

02:27.973 --> 02:30.672
- Did you see their faces?

02:30.715 --> 02:33.153
- Their faces were covered.
There were no cameras.

02:33.196 --> 02:34.937
They didn't say a word.
They were smart.

02:34.980 --> 02:37.374
- Okay, let me find them--
- You can't go to IAD.

02:37.418 --> 02:39.637
I'm guessing they've already
got a open case on me.

02:39.681 --> 02:41.683
Nolan has men inside,
so we can't trust that.

02:41.726 --> 02:44.164
And I have absolutely
nothing on them still.

02:44.207 --> 02:45.861
- Which is why
I'd go elsewhere.

02:45.904 --> 02:47.341
- I appreciate that,

02:47.384 --> 02:48.951
but this is what
we knew was coming.

02:48.994 --> 02:51.214
- Kev, there are ways--

02:51.258 --> 02:53.085
- Sarge, we already
talked about this.

02:53.129 --> 02:54.217
And I already talked
to the team.

02:54.261 --> 02:56.741
I can handle them.
I'm good.

03:00.789 --> 03:02.356
- Okay.

03:02.399 --> 03:05.010
Well, come on.
We caught a case.

03:05.054 --> 03:10.364
♪

03:10.407 --> 03:11.843
- Sergeant Voight.

03:11.887 --> 03:13.802
911 call came in
about eight minutes ago.

03:13.845 --> 03:15.891
- What was the call?
- Injured female.

03:15.934 --> 03:17.501
A male caller
reporting his friend hurt.

03:17.545 --> 03:19.503
Patrol arrived, entered,
found a deceased female.

03:19.547 --> 03:21.505
- Okay.
- Male caller inside with her.

03:21.549 --> 03:24.378
Sir, the male inside
is Billy Braddem.

03:24.421 --> 03:27.685
- As in Alderman Braddem?
- It's his son.

03:27.729 --> 03:31.341
- The ex-cop, right?
- Yup.

03:31.385 --> 03:32.690
Talk to me.
- She was already stiff.

03:32.734 --> 03:34.823
Died hours ago.
Probably around 2:00 a.m.

03:34.866 --> 03:36.694
Kid won't move.
He's high out of his mind.

03:36.738 --> 03:38.218
- You want us to help her,
you need to let her go.

03:38.261 --> 03:40.742
- Found him like this?
- Yeah.

03:40.785 --> 03:42.222
- Listen to me...
- Hey, hey.

03:42.265 --> 03:44.006
- Or I'll have to remove you.
- I got it, we got it.

03:44.049 --> 03:46.226
Kev.
- She needs help.

03:46.269 --> 03:47.879
I can hear her breathing.

03:47.923 --> 03:49.925
- Hey. Billy, I'm Kev.
Can you look at me?

03:49.968 --> 03:52.710
- [panting and whimpering]

03:52.754 --> 03:54.277
She's breathing.

03:54.321 --> 03:57.541
- I can hear her too.
I can hear her.

03:57.585 --> 03:59.630
I'm gonna step closer
so I can hear her better,

03:59.674 --> 04:01.589
but I need you to let her go.

04:01.632 --> 04:03.373
Here.
Set the knife down.

04:03.417 --> 04:05.157
- [whimpers]
- We wanna help her.

04:05.201 --> 04:06.985
So just put the knife down.

04:07.029 --> 04:09.292
You gotta work with us.
- [whimpers]

04:09.336 --> 04:12.382
- Billy, listen to me.
Just like that.

04:12.426 --> 04:14.950
Uh-huh, there you go.
There you go.

04:14.993 --> 04:16.560
Yeah, we're good.

04:16.604 --> 04:18.388
All right?
We just wanna help her.

04:18.432 --> 04:20.869
- We're gonna help her.
- I love her, I love--

04:20.912 --> 04:23.567
- Come on, okay, okay.
- [whimpers]

04:23.611 --> 04:25.221
Please help her, please.

04:25.265 --> 04:27.005
- There you go.
- [panting]

04:27.049 --> 04:29.269
[whimpers]
- Yeah.

04:29.312 --> 04:32.228
[somber music]

04:32.272 --> 04:36.319
♪

04:37.581 --> 04:39.844
- The victim's IDed
as Isla Sherman,

04:39.888 --> 04:41.368
18 years of age.

04:41.411 --> 04:43.457
She's got a few priors
for drug possession as a juvie,

04:43.500 --> 04:45.415
but other than that, I mean,
she's a bit of a ghost.

04:45.459 --> 04:46.895
- It looks like
she was an addict.

04:46.938 --> 04:49.332
No LKAs in years other
than the place that she died.

04:49.376 --> 04:50.768
- You locate the family?
- Yeah.

04:50.812 --> 04:52.640
I tracked her mom down
to Arizona.

04:52.683 --> 04:54.729
She was surprised Isla
was still alive actually.

04:54.772 --> 04:56.818
Written her off as dead
a long time ago.

04:56.861 --> 04:59.429
Won't be claiming the body.
- And what about Billy?

04:59.473 --> 05:01.257
- Oh, with him,
I had to do some digging.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.129
Alderman Braddem never mentions
Billy in his stump speeches.

05:04.173 --> 05:05.261
Kid's never one of the sons

05:05.305 --> 05:06.436
standing behind him
at the podium.

05:06.480 --> 05:08.351
He's got no public traces.

05:08.395 --> 05:09.831
I did find him logged
as a patient

05:09.874 --> 05:11.833
at more than a dozen rehabs,
though.

05:11.876 --> 05:13.835
- Yeah, his school records
are a mess.

05:13.878 --> 05:15.706
I mean, this kid's been in
and out of a different school

05:15.750 --> 05:17.186
every year since he was 14.

05:17.229 --> 05:21.321
- Huh, so we think Braddem
kicked him out of the house?

05:21.364 --> 05:23.279
- Yeah, I mean,
that would be my guess.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.499
I can't figure out his
relationship to Isla, though.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.892
Friends, boyfriend,
maybe they just use together?

05:27.936 --> 05:30.808
I'm scouring social media--
- Hey.

05:30.852 --> 05:33.594
She's been waiting for you
for over an hour.

05:33.637 --> 05:35.639
We're halfway to that
being her permanent office,

05:35.683 --> 05:38.163
so could you, please?

05:38.207 --> 05:40.731
Yeah, I'm back.

05:42.342 --> 05:43.473
- Deputy.
- [sighs]

05:43.517 --> 05:45.388
Have you got any baking soda
in your office?

05:45.432 --> 05:47.521
- I don't.

05:47.564 --> 05:50.567
- One of those stain pens?
- Sorry.

05:50.611 --> 05:51.699
- [sighs]
That's a shame.

05:51.742 --> 05:53.396
I read
your crime scene report--

05:53.440 --> 05:54.963
- You wanna know
if I know the Alderman?

05:55.006 --> 05:58.314
I'm just guessing
where this is headed.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.882
The answer's no, I've
never met Alderman Braddem.

06:00.925 --> 06:03.624
- Okay, because this is
one of those instances

06:03.667 --> 06:06.366
where CPD must enact equality
in law enforcement.

06:06.409 --> 06:07.497
- Sure.

06:07.541 --> 06:08.933
- Meaning absolutely
zero Blue Wall

06:08.977 --> 06:11.719
or preferential treatment
for an Alderman's son.

06:11.762 --> 06:13.460
- Yeah, lucky
I never met the man.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.897
I won't be protecting his son.
- Okay, great.

06:15.940 --> 06:18.421
And I'm still gonna ask you
to press murder charges ASAP.

06:18.465 --> 06:20.858
- You know, questioning an
offender who's not coherent--

06:20.902 --> 06:23.208
- Is better than affording
an offender an extra 12 hours

06:23.252 --> 06:24.427
before questioning.

06:24.471 --> 06:27.038
- To get sober.
- Or to rehearse.

06:27.082 --> 06:28.692
- Mm.
- Look.

06:28.736 --> 06:31.086
We're gonna treat his kid
like any other offender.

06:31.129 --> 06:34.045
You take his blood,
you document his tox,

06:34.089 --> 06:37.222
question him, and charge.

06:37.266 --> 06:39.877
ASAP.

06:39.921 --> 06:43.446
You know, we don't have
to go 12 rounds every time.

06:43.490 --> 06:45.013
I'm gonna give you an order.
That's my job.

06:45.056 --> 06:46.144
But we can be nice.

06:46.188 --> 06:48.973
Can you see this?

06:49.017 --> 06:50.061
- I can.

06:50.105 --> 06:52.324
- Is it see-through?

06:52.368 --> 06:54.631
- It is.
[phone rings]

06:54.675 --> 06:57.504
- Okay.
Deputy Miller.

06:58.505 --> 07:01.595
- Hmm.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.161
Hey, Billy.
[smacks table]

07:03.205 --> 07:05.599
Billy, look at me.

07:05.642 --> 07:06.817
Look at me.

07:06.861 --> 07:09.429
I'm Sergeant Hank Voight
with the CPD.

07:09.472 --> 07:11.474
- Hey, Billy.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.128
Do you remember me?
We were just downstairs.

07:13.171 --> 07:16.392
We just talked.

07:16.436 --> 07:19.047
- Boy, this kid's got no
short-term memory whatsoever.

07:19.090 --> 07:20.918
- I don't even think
he knows where he is.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.790
- Billy, do you know
why you're here?

07:22.833 --> 07:25.009
- Isla?
- Mm-hmm.

07:25.053 --> 07:27.403
- Where is she?
- She's dead.

07:27.447 --> 07:31.146
Can you tell us
what happened to her?

07:31.189 --> 07:32.930
Hey, Billy.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.715
Billy!

07:34.758 --> 07:37.674
The way we found you
with the knife,

07:37.718 --> 07:40.808
this is a bad situation,
do you understand?

07:40.851 --> 07:43.637
- Do you think I killed her?
- I do.

07:43.680 --> 07:45.203
- All right,
this death looks like

07:45.247 --> 07:47.336
what we call
a crime of passion, Billy.

07:47.379 --> 07:49.991
Like a fight broke out,
something went wrong,

07:50.034 --> 07:51.688
a knife was grabbed
from the kitchen.

07:51.732 --> 07:54.604
- I didn't kill her.
The--the man killed her.

07:54.648 --> 07:56.301
- Okay, the man.
What man?

07:56.345 --> 07:59.087
- The man in the apartment.
He killed her.

07:59.130 --> 08:03.047
- Who was he?
- I don't know.

08:03.091 --> 08:05.310
- Can you describe
what he looked like?

08:05.354 --> 08:07.225
- He was white.

08:07.269 --> 08:11.969
He was in his 40s.
He...had green eyes.

08:12.013 --> 08:15.756
He was wearing a suit.
White shirt.

08:15.799 --> 08:18.323
Blue tie
with red stripes on it.

08:18.367 --> 08:20.500
He had this voice like...

08:20.543 --> 08:23.764
It was really light.

08:23.807 --> 08:26.636
And like
he was telling a story.

08:26.680 --> 08:29.900
Like he knew
what he wanted to say, and...

08:31.598 --> 08:35.123
- You ever seen
this man before?

08:35.166 --> 08:36.733
- Can I see Isla?

08:36.777 --> 08:39.780
- She's dead, Billy.

08:39.823 --> 08:43.000
[soft dramatic music]

08:43.044 --> 08:45.350
- I just wanna see her again.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.657
Please, just...

08:47.701 --> 08:50.181
tell me where you put her.

08:50.225 --> 08:54.882
♪

08:54.925 --> 08:57.493
- You ever hear a suspect
description that detailed?

08:57.537 --> 09:00.409
- No.
Maybe it's the high talking.

09:00.452 --> 09:02.019
- Mm-hmm.
- That detailed?

09:02.063 --> 09:04.065
- Or telling his own story.

09:04.108 --> 09:05.980
- I just feel like you gotta be
some amount of "here"

09:06.023 --> 09:07.808
to come up with that,
and whether it's true or not,

09:07.851 --> 09:09.549
it seems like he believes it.

09:09.592 --> 09:10.680
And he asked to see the body.

09:10.724 --> 09:12.552
That's not
normal offender behavior.

09:12.595 --> 09:13.770
- Addicts' behavior
doesn't always

09:13.814 --> 09:14.815
match their truth, though.

09:14.858 --> 09:16.251
They know how to lie.

09:16.294 --> 09:18.209
- I suppose he could be
feeding us a fake suspect.

09:18.253 --> 09:19.863
- I don't know.

09:19.907 --> 09:23.475
And we're not gonna know more
until he's sober.

09:23.519 --> 09:25.390
Well, he gave us
another suspect.

09:25.434 --> 09:26.478
Let's run it.

09:26.522 --> 09:27.741
- You really wanna wait
to charge?

09:27.784 --> 09:29.786
- Until we know he's guilty,
yeah.

09:32.136 --> 09:35.096
[tense music]

09:35.139 --> 09:40.797
♪

09:40.841 --> 09:42.625
- There's really nothing
that would indicate

09:42.669 --> 09:45.236
there was a third person
in the apartment.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.456
We got two sets of takeout

09:47.499 --> 09:50.546
and beers
surrounding two chairs.

09:50.590 --> 09:54.724
- Two sets of the works.
- Not much here.

09:54.768 --> 09:58.336
- This place is tiny.

09:58.380 --> 09:59.860
- I know, I really don't see

09:59.903 --> 10:01.296
how somebody
could be hiding out.

10:01.339 --> 10:04.734
And the blood splatter
indicates just one offender.

10:04.778 --> 10:05.953
[TV chatter]

10:05.996 --> 10:07.781
- TV was on
at the time of death.

10:07.824 --> 10:10.261
- Yeah, Forensics hasn't
dusted this room yet.

10:10.305 --> 10:11.741
[indistinct chatter]

10:11.785 --> 10:14.744
- They are expected to rise
based on positive...

10:14.788 --> 10:16.572
- We just wanted
to circle back,

10:16.616 --> 10:18.052
make sure Patrol
didn't miss anything.

10:18.095 --> 10:20.489
You see anything unusual?
Any visitors?

10:20.532 --> 10:22.665
- The car was unusual.
- A car?

10:22.709 --> 10:25.668
All right.
What car is that?

10:25.712 --> 10:27.191
- I don't know.
It looked blue, maybe?

10:27.235 --> 10:29.541
2:00 a.m., it just sat out
there wasting gas.

10:29.585 --> 10:31.021
Headlights blaring
through my window.

10:31.065 --> 10:32.196
- Did you see anyone
in the car,

10:32.240 --> 10:33.937
or anyone enter
or exit the apartment?

10:33.981 --> 10:36.244
- No, just the car.
I took my dog out.

10:36.287 --> 10:37.941
By the time I came back,
it sped away,

10:37.985 --> 10:39.726
but it sat out there
20 minutes.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.162
- Why didn't you mention this
to Patrol?

10:41.205 --> 10:42.859
- No Patrol ever came by.
I've been home all day.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.252
Nobody's talked to me.

10:44.295 --> 10:45.775
She died, didn't she?

10:45.819 --> 10:48.299
That young girl?
- Yes, ma'am.

10:48.343 --> 10:50.214
- She seemed
like a good person.

10:50.258 --> 10:54.262
Seemed like she tried real hard
to be happy.

10:54.305 --> 10:56.133
- I don't understand.
Where is my son?

10:56.177 --> 10:58.701
- Sir, your son's upstairs.
- Upstairs.

10:58.745 --> 11:01.486
You've got him in a box?
You found him high?

11:01.530 --> 11:03.010
- Yes, sir.
He was high.

11:03.053 --> 11:04.838
- You're questioning my son
without a lawyer

11:04.881 --> 11:06.187
while he's high.

11:06.230 --> 11:08.145
Are you kidding me?
- Hey, hey, hey!

11:08.189 --> 11:10.452
- Why the hell is he upstairs
without a lawyer?

11:10.495 --> 11:12.889
- Listen, I'm happy to talk--
- I am gonna have your badge.

11:12.933 --> 11:15.239
- I'm just doing my job.
- You won't be for much longer.

11:15.283 --> 11:17.415
I will tear you apart
in front of the media.

11:17.459 --> 11:20.201
And I know who you are.
I know how you police.

11:20.244 --> 11:22.725
- Alderman Braddem.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.858
Deputy Superintendent Miller.

11:24.901 --> 11:27.295
- I want to see my kid.
I need to be in there.

11:27.338 --> 11:29.732
- And I will help you do that,
just not in the hallway

11:29.776 --> 11:31.778
and not while
raising our voices.

11:31.821 --> 11:33.997
Right this way.

11:34.041 --> 11:36.739
[low dramatic music]

11:36.783 --> 11:38.828
♪

11:38.872 --> 11:42.005
I'll speak to you upstairs.

11:46.096 --> 11:48.229
- McKenzie, you just came here
to watch?

11:48.272 --> 11:55.236
♪

11:59.022 --> 12:00.371
That was clearly leaked
to Alderman.

12:00.415 --> 12:02.809
- Well, it doesn't matter how.
We're here now.

12:02.852 --> 12:04.375
Tell me we got something.

12:04.419 --> 12:06.769
- I confirmed a blue Sedan
outside Isla's apartment

12:06.813 --> 12:07.944
around the time of death.

12:07.988 --> 12:09.598
Caught it coming and going.

12:09.641 --> 12:10.860
Matches
the witness' time frame,

12:10.904 --> 12:12.514
but there's no POD
outside of Isla's.

12:12.557 --> 12:14.081
So the car turns
into her block,

12:14.124 --> 12:16.387
I lose it, and I catch it
leaving 20 minutes later.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.041
- So we can't
confirm the plates

12:18.085 --> 12:19.347
or that it was
even outside of Isla's.

12:19.390 --> 12:21.044
It's possible
somebody exited the car,

12:21.088 --> 12:23.394
went into the apartment, but
we have zero way to prove that.

12:23.438 --> 12:26.006
- Hey, I think I got something.
- Okay.

12:26.049 --> 12:28.095
- TV was on in Isla's apartment
last night,

12:28.138 --> 12:30.793
so I followed a feeling,
and this was playing

12:30.837 --> 12:32.534
during the time of death.

12:32.577 --> 12:34.492
- Was first indicated
in the city's loop, and has--

12:34.536 --> 12:37.147
- White male, 40s.
Grey hair, green eyes.

12:37.191 --> 12:38.932
Blue and red tie.
Suit.

12:38.975 --> 12:41.369
- And a voice
like he's telling a story.

12:41.412 --> 12:43.588
- [sighs]
Can happen during trauma.

12:43.632 --> 12:46.243
Brain's wires get crossed,
latches onto the wrong thing.

12:46.287 --> 12:47.592
- Officials report
this trend--

12:47.636 --> 12:50.291
- I don't think Billy has
any idea what's real.

12:50.334 --> 12:52.772
- Hmm.

12:56.645 --> 12:56.819
.

12:56.863 --> 12:59.082
- Over 12 hours
on an open and shut scene,

12:59.126 --> 13:01.519
and now we've got
an ex-cop Alderman

13:01.563 --> 13:05.001
in the 21st, meeting
with his son's investigator.

13:05.045 --> 13:07.830
You disobeyed a direct order.
- Because it wasn't real.

13:07.874 --> 13:10.224
- If I give you an order,
it's real.

13:10.267 --> 13:14.271
- No, not if you don't tell me
why you're giving it to me.

13:14.315 --> 13:16.708
- That kid was found
holding the murder weapon

13:16.752 --> 13:18.536
laying next to the dead girl.
- I'm aware.

13:18.580 --> 13:19.973
- And yet,
you haven't charged him.

13:20.016 --> 13:21.539
- What if that kid in there
were Black?

13:21.583 --> 13:24.804
Would you be ordering me
to charge ASAP?

13:24.847 --> 13:28.285
'Cause I think if that were an
18-year-old Black kid in there

13:28.329 --> 13:31.288
with no rich family,
no politician father,

13:31.332 --> 13:33.203
you wouldn't be
pressing me to charge

13:33.247 --> 13:35.336
until I had the whole of it,

13:35.379 --> 13:37.773
until it felt right.

13:37.817 --> 13:40.689
But he's white,
he's privileged,

13:40.732 --> 13:42.822
and you're damn scared
the media's gonna

13:42.865 --> 13:45.825
hand you your ass
your first month of work.

13:47.522 --> 13:50.220
I don't care who his father is.

13:50.264 --> 13:52.788
You do.

13:54.877 --> 13:56.879
- All right.

13:56.923 --> 13:59.621
You take the full 48
if you need to.

14:01.623 --> 14:03.103
I'll make sure you can have it.

14:03.146 --> 14:06.106
[eerie music]

14:06.149 --> 14:07.324
♪

14:07.368 --> 14:10.327
- No.

14:10.371 --> 14:13.591
No, it's not possible.
It was real.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.376
I-I know
I was screwed up, okay?

14:15.419 --> 14:16.899
But--but I'm clear now.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.814
Maybe...maybe
it wasn't this man.

14:18.858 --> 14:21.991
Fine, but someone was there.
- Billy.

14:22.035 --> 14:25.821
Are you sober now?

14:25.865 --> 14:26.996
Okay, understand this.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.606
We got about 32 hours

14:28.650 --> 14:30.957
till we have to either
charge or release you.

14:31.000 --> 14:33.611
- I didn't do this!
- That, I don't know.

14:33.655 --> 14:36.571
What I do know is your father
and your lawyer are downstairs

14:36.614 --> 14:39.269
right now, and I'm obligated
to bring your lawyer up here.

14:39.313 --> 14:41.358
- My dad's here?
- Mm-hmm.

14:41.402 --> 14:43.578
- And he brought
his whole team of lawyers?

14:43.621 --> 14:48.235
[scoffs]
He thinks I did this.

14:48.278 --> 14:50.280
No.
No, you know what?

14:50.324 --> 14:53.153
I...
I don't want his lawyers.

14:53.196 --> 14:55.459
I don't want his help.
Go ahead.

14:55.503 --> 14:59.376
I-I know there's a form
I can sign.

14:59.420 --> 15:00.900
- You're declining
representation?

15:00.943 --> 15:02.684
- Yes.

15:02.727 --> 15:05.426
I don't know what happened.

15:05.469 --> 15:09.952
I don't remember,
but I didn't kill Isla.

15:09.996 --> 15:13.129
So go ahead.

15:13.173 --> 15:15.523
Ask me whatever you want.

15:15.566 --> 15:17.394
- The first time
Billy entered rehab

15:17.438 --> 15:20.049
was a month shy
of his 14th birthday.

15:20.093 --> 15:24.010
- My dad, he--he wanted
to help me, fix me.

15:24.053 --> 15:26.447
Rehab, military schools,

15:26.490 --> 15:27.839
religious camps,

15:27.883 --> 15:29.624
some shaman that tried
to starve it out of me,

15:29.667 --> 15:32.148
but none of it worked.

15:32.192 --> 15:33.497
[inhales]

15:33.541 --> 15:35.499
Then I met Isla at a meeting.

15:35.543 --> 15:36.979
- And unfortunately,
Isla didn't have

15:37.023 --> 15:39.677
the money or the father
that Billy had.

15:39.721 --> 15:41.766
No rehab--just
possession charges, shelters.

15:41.810 --> 15:43.420
She was totally alone
in all this.

15:43.464 --> 15:46.206
- Isla quit going to meetings.

15:46.249 --> 15:48.512
You know, she thought
she was good.

15:48.556 --> 15:52.255
For some reason,
she thought I was good too.

15:52.299 --> 15:54.344
That we could do it together.

15:54.388 --> 15:56.303
Just her and I.

15:56.346 --> 15:58.348
We tried.

15:58.392 --> 16:00.524
And it worked.

16:00.568 --> 16:03.179
- So you were sober until--
- Last night.

16:03.223 --> 16:04.876
- Hmm.

16:04.920 --> 16:07.705
- We had a year.

16:07.749 --> 16:09.881
- It's hard
to confirm sobriety,

16:09.925 --> 16:12.014
but it does look
like Isla's life changed.

16:12.058 --> 16:14.538
So this is her before.

16:14.582 --> 16:17.019
She seems to have a pretty
small circle of friends.

16:17.063 --> 16:19.804
Most of her posts are
about drugs and parties.

16:19.848 --> 16:22.503
And then, right around the time
that Billy says they met,

16:22.546 --> 16:25.027
a new set of friends,
lots of photos.

16:25.071 --> 16:26.811
She looks happy.

16:26.855 --> 16:29.379
- Also around that time,
she opens a bank account.

16:29.423 --> 16:31.729
Gets a job, the apartment.

16:31.773 --> 16:34.471
- I think they really did
change each other.

16:34.515 --> 16:37.300
- Now take me through it
one more time.

16:37.344 --> 16:40.042
Last night...
- Isla texted me.

16:40.086 --> 16:41.522
She said she was bad.

16:41.565 --> 16:43.219
That's all.
I knew what she meant.

16:43.263 --> 16:46.266
It's what we would do if we
felt like we were coming apart,

16:46.309 --> 16:47.745
itching to use.

16:47.789 --> 16:50.705
We'd talk each other
off the ledge.

16:50.748 --> 16:54.187
- She asked you over?

16:54.230 --> 16:55.971
- All right,
so we're still running towers,

16:56.015 --> 16:57.146
but it looks like

16:57.190 --> 17:00.889
Isla texted Billy at 6:45.

17:00.932 --> 17:02.412
He called her back
two minutes later.

17:02.456 --> 17:05.067
Arrived at her place at 8:00.
- And they were alone?

17:05.111 --> 17:07.243
- According to Billy,
nobody else in the apartment.

17:07.287 --> 17:09.637
Just Isla and the drugs.

17:09.680 --> 17:12.074
- She already had the heroin
on her?

17:12.118 --> 17:15.121
- Yeah, she had
a black duffel bag.

17:15.164 --> 17:17.601
Dope was already out of it.
- Uh-huh.

17:17.645 --> 17:21.866
- Then we used.

17:21.910 --> 17:23.433
We drank.

17:23.477 --> 17:27.089
A year of sobriety
gone in a second.

17:27.133 --> 17:29.048
And then, I can't really
remember it all from there.

17:29.091 --> 17:32.921
Um...I know we were together
in the kitchen.

17:32.964 --> 17:34.009
- Okay.

17:34.053 --> 17:38.057
- And then,
I was in the bedroom.

17:38.100 --> 17:40.363
I woke up to voices.

17:40.407 --> 17:42.017
Someone was mad at her.
A man.

17:42.061 --> 17:44.759
I could see someone there.
- Okay, what were they saying?

17:44.802 --> 17:47.544
- I don't know.
I just...

17:47.588 --> 17:48.980
I woke up again.

17:49.024 --> 17:53.115
She was on the ground,
wet and bloody.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.900
I-I tried to help her.

17:55.944 --> 17:58.686
I think I pulled the knife out.

18:01.036 --> 18:02.820
- Once he's high,
we can't confirm any of it.

18:02.864 --> 18:04.735
There's no black duffel bag
at the scene.

18:04.779 --> 18:07.216
- No reports from neighbors
hearing any arguing,

18:07.260 --> 18:08.826
no signs of forced entry.

18:08.870 --> 18:10.393
- Right,
so what about the knife?

18:10.437 --> 18:12.439
If he pulled it, Forensics
should be able to confirm it.

18:12.482 --> 18:13.570
- No, we're dead there.

18:13.614 --> 18:15.050
Forensics ruled the knife
inconclusive.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.486
Blood and prints
were contaminated.

18:16.530 --> 18:17.879
- So what else we got?

18:17.922 --> 18:19.272
Hmm?
- Not much.

18:19.315 --> 18:21.970
We can't confirm anyone
was inside the apartment

18:22.013 --> 18:23.319
besides Billy.

18:23.363 --> 18:25.582
- Here's an odd thing--
I ran Isla's cell phone.

18:25.626 --> 18:27.149
Everything matches
with Billy's story,

18:27.193 --> 18:29.586
except for when she texted him
to tell him she felt bad,

18:29.630 --> 18:31.110
she was all the way out
in Lake Forest.

18:31.153 --> 18:33.460
- Lake Forest?
She has connections out there?

18:33.503 --> 18:34.722
- Billy never mentioned
anything,

18:34.765 --> 18:36.027
but the phone tagged
her location.

18:36.071 --> 18:37.507
She was definitely there.
- All right.

18:37.551 --> 18:38.595
Good.
Let's run with that.

18:38.639 --> 18:41.685
Go.
Come on.

18:41.729 --> 18:43.034
- I'm so sorry.
Nobody was here.

18:43.078 --> 18:45.124
I don't even know anybody
named Isla.

18:45.167 --> 18:46.690
- Okay.

18:46.734 --> 18:48.692
Well, have you seen any cars
in the area since yesterday?

18:48.736 --> 18:51.042
Anything unusual?
- No.

18:51.086 --> 18:53.349
This place is pretty much
the definition of ordinary.

18:53.393 --> 18:54.611
I'm sorry.

18:54.655 --> 18:56.744
- What's with
this hidden camera here?

18:56.787 --> 18:59.355
- It's probably
just a kid's toy, or--

18:59.399 --> 19:01.705
- [grunts]
No.

19:04.012 --> 19:07.755
It's a hidden security system.
- I just rent the property.

19:07.798 --> 19:10.236
- Hadley, you're gonna
stay down here with me.

19:10.279 --> 19:13.587
Come on.

19:13.630 --> 19:17.373
- [sighs]
You smell that?

19:17.417 --> 19:19.593
- Acetone.

19:19.636 --> 19:21.508
[quiet tense music]

19:21.551 --> 19:24.206
What you got?

19:24.250 --> 19:27.383
[grunts]

19:27.427 --> 19:34.347
♪

19:37.741 --> 19:41.180
Clear.

19:41.223 --> 19:43.051
- 5021 Ida,

19:43.094 --> 19:44.966
I got a confirmation on
my narcotics call.

19:45.009 --> 19:46.968
Gonna need backup and Forensics

19:47.011 --> 19:50.232
to 163 North Sheridan.
- Copy that...

19:50.276 --> 19:52.756
- About a million dollars
worth.

19:52.800 --> 19:55.237
- I'd say.

19:55.281 --> 19:58.414
[phone buzzes]

19:58.458 --> 20:00.503
- Jordan?

20:00.547 --> 20:02.897
Jordan.

20:02.940 --> 20:06.292
Jordan, why are you calling me
from the landline?

20:06.335 --> 20:09.164
What?

20:09.208 --> 20:11.122
Our security alarm
just went off.

20:11.166 --> 20:12.994
- All right, well, go.
- Are you sure?

20:13.037 --> 20:16.563
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- Jordan, I'm on my way.

20:16.606 --> 20:18.217
Jordan, where you at?

20:18.260 --> 20:19.653
- They said
it's probably tripped.

20:19.696 --> 20:21.089
- Let me see your phone.
- What, why?

20:21.132 --> 20:22.264
- You said that
it was burning hot

20:22.308 --> 20:23.787
and that the battery
was dying, right?

20:23.831 --> 20:25.528
They bugged you.

20:25.572 --> 20:26.964
Mm-hmm.
- Bugged?

20:27.008 --> 20:28.836
- There's static
on this line too.

20:28.879 --> 20:30.490
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- They bugged both phones.

20:30.533 --> 20:33.275
- Who bugged us?
- Shh.

20:33.319 --> 20:35.146
- What?

20:35.190 --> 20:37.279
- The cops.

20:37.323 --> 20:39.803
♪

20:39.847 --> 20:41.283
Give me your phone.
- What?

20:41.327 --> 20:43.024
They ain't bugging me, man.
- Give me your phone.

20:43.067 --> 20:45.722
- They ain't bugging me.
Okay, okay.

20:45.766 --> 20:46.984
All right,
all right, all right.

20:47.028 --> 20:48.899
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
Stop, man, stop.

20:48.943 --> 20:50.945
- Sorry, Jordan,
but they were in here.

20:50.988 --> 20:54.470
They've been playing with me
all day.

20:54.514 --> 20:57.038
I know what's going on--
know what's going on...

20:57.081 --> 20:58.866
Kev, security said
this happens all the time.

20:58.909 --> 21:00.433
- I know exactly
what's going on.

21:00.476 --> 21:01.825
They're cops.

21:01.869 --> 21:03.436
You don't think I know
what they're doing?

21:03.479 --> 21:05.829
- Kev, Kev!

21:05.873 --> 21:09.398
- They were in here.
They were in here.

21:09.442 --> 21:13.010
I know what they do.
I know what's going on.

21:13.054 --> 21:16.231
[gasps]
I know what they do.

21:16.275 --> 21:19.234
[tense music]

21:19.278 --> 21:26.197
♪

21:39.863 --> 21:40.299
.

21:40.342 --> 21:42.953
- Okay.

21:42.997 --> 21:44.172
- Hey.
- Hey, what's up?

21:44.215 --> 21:46.174
Look, they accessed
the side window.

21:46.217 --> 21:47.393
And I don't have
a direct image,

21:47.436 --> 21:48.872
but I do have a partial
on this black SUV.

21:48.916 --> 21:51.179
Can't tell whether
this is a cop car or not,

21:51.222 --> 21:54.313
and I can't make out
this guy's face.

21:54.356 --> 21:56.315
- Well, we could add
more cameras.

21:56.358 --> 21:58.055
- Man, they gotta be
feeding this to IAD,

21:58.099 --> 22:00.275
trying to find some dirt.

22:00.319 --> 22:02.843
They're working every angle,
ain't they?

22:02.886 --> 22:04.497
- Hey, Kev, maybe...

22:04.540 --> 22:08.588
we need to find a way
out of this thing now.

22:08.631 --> 22:09.893
- What you mean?

22:09.937 --> 22:12.113
- Nolan and McKenzie are
third generation police.

22:12.156 --> 22:14.724
I mean, there's gotta be some
sort of deal that they'd take.

22:14.768 --> 22:18.206
- Oh, and you talked to Voight?
- No.

22:18.249 --> 22:19.990
- Your dad?
- My dad?

22:20.034 --> 22:21.818
What the hell
would I talk to my dad for?

22:21.862 --> 22:24.386
- Third generation.
Ain't this what y'all do?

22:24.430 --> 22:28.390
- Kev, they are
coming after you, okay?

22:28.434 --> 22:29.913
If there's something
that we can give them--

22:29.957 --> 22:32.351
- Huh, give them?
I'm not giving them anything.

22:32.394 --> 22:34.353
I did nothing wrong.

22:34.396 --> 22:36.703
I told the truth.
They jumped me.

22:36.746 --> 22:38.357
Four against one.
Kicked my head in.

22:38.400 --> 22:39.836
Then broke into my house,
where I live,

22:39.880 --> 22:40.750
where my family lives.

22:40.794 --> 22:43.753
- Hey.
We still got a case.

22:43.797 --> 22:45.494
Still got a clock.

22:45.538 --> 22:48.715
[unsettling music]

22:48.758 --> 22:52.283
♪

22:52.327 --> 22:53.676
Get anything on Hadley?
- No.

22:53.720 --> 22:55.504
She claims she's never
been in the basement before,

22:55.548 --> 22:57.419
doesn't even have a key.
It's all a lie, of course.

22:57.463 --> 22:58.942
She knows exactly
who the drugs belong to.

22:58.986 --> 23:00.335
She lawyered up.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.424
Bag house is on bad paper.

23:02.468 --> 23:05.035
The owner registered it
to a bogus LLC.

23:05.079 --> 23:07.734
- All right, so me and Kev are
gonna run all that past Billy.

23:07.777 --> 23:10.998
Meantime, you get Hadley
into holding.

23:11.041 --> 23:13.392
Who is she?

23:13.435 --> 23:15.176
- I don't know, okay?

23:15.219 --> 23:17.308
I don't know this woman.

23:17.352 --> 23:18.832
I've never seen her!

23:18.875 --> 23:21.269
I-I told you
everything I can remember.

23:21.312 --> 23:23.140
You're telling me
you can't prove it.

23:23.184 --> 23:24.838
- Did Isla
ever mention a Hadley?

23:24.881 --> 23:26.666
Ever tell you where
she scored her drugs?

23:26.709 --> 23:28.407
- I've told you
everything I can remember.

23:28.450 --> 23:30.060
I can't--
- Hey, Billy.

23:30.104 --> 23:32.454
Billy, I know you're feeling
the pressure right now.

23:32.498 --> 23:34.717
All right, because
we are running out of time--

23:34.761 --> 23:36.545
- You think
I don't wanna remember?

23:36.589 --> 23:38.329
- Okay, well, just calm down.

23:38.373 --> 23:40.331
Okay, you can take this.
You can handle it.

23:40.375 --> 23:42.682
- My body feels terrible.

23:42.725 --> 23:45.641
I-I feel like
I'm losing my mind.

23:45.685 --> 23:47.687
- I know, but this is
where you fight, okay?

23:47.730 --> 23:49.776
This is where you fight, okay?

23:49.819 --> 23:53.257
- [inhales, exhales]
- Okay?

23:53.301 --> 23:55.825
All right,
all right, all right.

23:55.869 --> 23:59.394
Now, you don't know Hadley.
That's fine.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.309
What about the drugs?

24:01.352 --> 24:04.007
What about the heroin?

24:04.051 --> 24:05.705
- The tag.
- Okay.

24:05.748 --> 24:08.751
The tag.
- The insignia?

24:08.795 --> 24:10.318
- Yeah.
- Okay, what about it?

24:10.361 --> 24:12.015
- Yeah.
- Okay.

24:12.059 --> 24:14.322
- These bags of dope, they were
in the black bag.

24:14.365 --> 24:16.455
She had a lot of them.

24:16.498 --> 24:18.457
- Wait, you're saying
that she had

24:18.500 --> 24:20.502
more than just a few grams?

24:20.546 --> 24:22.417
- Yeah, the black bag
was full of these bags.

24:22.461 --> 24:25.376
[solemn music]

24:25.420 --> 24:26.726
♪

24:26.769 --> 24:30.033
- Guys, I made a connection.
Check this out.

24:30.077 --> 24:32.688
This is Tim Rollins.
He's 36 years old.

24:32.732 --> 24:35.517
He's got a history of violence,
two priors for drug possession

24:35.561 --> 24:37.345
with intent to distribute
in Indiana.

24:37.388 --> 24:39.869
Now, Hadley has calls,
Venmo requests,

24:39.913 --> 24:41.392
and social media hits
with this guy.

24:41.436 --> 24:44.004
So does Isla.

24:44.047 --> 24:45.788
And her social media is loaded
with pictures

24:45.832 --> 24:48.791
of the two of them right up
until when she met Billy.

24:48.835 --> 24:51.402
- Ex-boyfriend.
- The drugs are definitely his.

24:51.446 --> 24:53.143
Isla knew it.
She was itching.

24:53.187 --> 24:55.189
She went back.
She stole the drugs.

24:55.232 --> 24:56.495
- Bring him in.

24:56.538 --> 24:59.498
[tense music]

24:59.541 --> 25:05.982
♪

25:06.026 --> 25:08.376
- Blue Sedan.

25:08.419 --> 25:10.987
- Mm-hmm.

25:11.031 --> 25:17.907
♪

25:17.951 --> 25:20.867
- It's been cleaned.
Bleach.

25:20.910 --> 25:22.521
Jay, Hailey.

25:22.564 --> 25:23.913
We dropped an anchor
on Tim's place.

25:23.957 --> 25:26.133
We got a blue Sedan
freshly scrubbed down.

25:26.176 --> 25:27.526
It's the exact match to the car

25:27.569 --> 25:29.005
idling outside
Isla's apartment.

25:29.049 --> 25:30.659
- Copy that.
We're nine minutes out.

25:30.703 --> 25:32.661
- We'll hold anchor
until you arrive.

25:32.705 --> 25:34.533
- Hmm?
- Yo.

25:34.576 --> 25:37.057
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

25:37.100 --> 25:39.407
Tim Rollins.

25:41.714 --> 25:43.977
- Hey, hey!
Stop!

25:44.020 --> 25:45.326
Chicago PD!

25:45.369 --> 25:46.588
I'ma go around the back!
- Copy.

25:46.632 --> 25:49.591
[suspenseful music]

25:49.635 --> 25:52.507
♪

25:52.551 --> 25:56.816
- 5021 Ida in foot pursuit.
Westbound alley towards Bell.

25:56.859 --> 25:59.862
Offender is male, white.
6'2" in blue jeans.

25:59.906 --> 26:01.864
I need patrol cars
off Bell and Waveland.

26:01.908 --> 26:05.389
I need containment right now.

26:05.433 --> 26:07.391
- Copy that, 5021 Ida.

26:07.435 --> 26:08.828
Units in your area.

26:08.871 --> 26:12.092
- 5021 Ida, I need an ETA
on that backup!

26:12.135 --> 26:14.703
- Hey!
- Watch out!

26:14.747 --> 26:17.358
- 5021 Ida,
units not responding.

26:17.401 --> 26:19.882
- Do I have containment or not?
Where is everyone?

26:19.926 --> 26:24.017
- Negative.
No one in route.

26:24.060 --> 26:27.107
♪

26:27.150 --> 26:28.630
- Dispatch,
do I have cars coming?

26:28.674 --> 26:30.414
Where the hell is my backup?

26:30.458 --> 26:32.591
I lost eyes.

26:32.634 --> 26:36.116
[gunshot fires]
- Adam!

26:37.813 --> 26:40.381
Adam!

26:40.424 --> 26:42.296
- [inhales, groans]

26:42.339 --> 26:43.776
- Adam?
5021, 10-1.

26:43.819 --> 26:45.734
10-1, shots fired.
Officer down.

26:45.778 --> 26:47.736
Roll an ambo
to the west alley of Bell.

26:47.780 --> 26:48.911
Where is he?
Where is he?

26:48.955 --> 26:50.391
Where is he?
- He's gone, he's gone.

26:50.434 --> 26:51.871
- You--let me get this off.
- Ah, I'm good, I'm good.

26:51.914 --> 26:54.047
- Shut up.
You don't know that.

26:54.090 --> 26:55.091
- [groans]

26:55.135 --> 26:56.397
- It didn't go through.
- I know.

26:56.440 --> 26:57.746
Rollins kept going.
You should go.

26:57.790 --> 26:59.574
- No, no, it hit your rib.
You breathing all right?

26:59.618 --> 27:01.315
- I'm fine.
The wind's just knocked--

27:01.358 --> 27:02.621
- Ruzek, where you at?

27:02.664 --> 27:04.057
- It's good, bro.
The vest took it.

27:04.100 --> 27:06.146
- What the hell happened?
- Hit the ribs.

27:06.189 --> 27:07.626
- [panting]

27:07.669 --> 27:08.888
I shouldn't have
taken the corner.

27:08.931 --> 27:12.500
Patrol never rolled.
- He's good.

27:12.543 --> 27:14.676
- [groans]

27:14.720 --> 27:17.331
- They're not rolling with me.
I'm sorry, bro.

27:17.374 --> 27:18.288
- It's all right.
- I'm good.

27:18.332 --> 27:19.638
- He's good.

27:19.681 --> 27:21.030
- No, you just got shot
'cause of me.

27:21.074 --> 27:22.945
- It's not on you, Kev.
You're good.

27:22.989 --> 27:25.861
- He just got shot.
He just got shot.

27:31.214 --> 27:31.432
.

27:31.475 --> 27:33.042
- Who didn't respond?
- Kevin.

27:33.086 --> 27:34.740
- I know it's on your radar.

27:34.783 --> 27:37.525
Who didn't respond to the call?
- Kevin, I am looking into it.

27:37.568 --> 27:39.570
I'm going to question
every officer--

27:39.614 --> 27:42.530
- Who was it?

27:42.573 --> 27:44.619
- There were three
patrol officers in the area

27:44.663 --> 27:45.751
and four tact guys.

27:45.794 --> 27:47.753
- Who were the tact guys?

27:47.796 --> 27:50.581
- Right now, every one of them
has plausible deniability--

27:50.625 --> 27:54.542
- Of course they do.
Who were the tact guys?

27:54.585 --> 27:57.110
- McKenzie was one of them.
Kevin, come on.

27:57.153 --> 27:59.068
Kevin, no.
Kevin, please...

27:59.112 --> 28:02.071
[tense music]

28:02.115 --> 28:05.901
♪

28:05.945 --> 28:07.468
- Really?

28:07.511 --> 28:10.079
This is what we're doing?
Letting cops get killed?

28:10.123 --> 28:12.603
- I was making an arrest.
- Ruzek got shot.

28:12.647 --> 28:14.910
- I couldn't roll on a call.
Back the hell up, man!

28:14.954 --> 28:16.999
- You feel good, huh?

28:17.043 --> 28:18.958
Coming at good cops
'cause I told the truth?

28:19.001 --> 28:20.437
- I'm not coming for you.

28:20.481 --> 28:22.396
- You just wanna watch officers
bleed out in the dirt--

28:22.439 --> 28:24.615
- I said I ain't coming--
- Yeah, you woke now?

28:24.659 --> 28:27.096
- I gave you your answer.
Now back up!

28:27.140 --> 28:29.403
- I ain't backing
no damn where, coward.

28:29.446 --> 28:31.622
- Whoa, hey.
- Hmm, huh?

28:31.666 --> 28:33.146
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, hey, hey.

28:33.189 --> 28:34.930
- You're still protecting
your racist ass buddy?

28:34.974 --> 28:36.889
- Not here, man.
- Hey!

28:36.932 --> 28:38.673
You take a breath.
It's us.

28:38.717 --> 28:42.068
Take a breath.
- He's giving orders.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.636
- [wheezes]
I'm good.

28:45.680 --> 28:47.638
- You think any of us
wanna be doing this?

28:47.682 --> 28:49.466
The world of police
is burning down.

28:49.510 --> 28:51.120
You think patrol cops
wanna be coming for you,

28:51.164 --> 28:54.645
risking their jobs?

28:54.689 --> 28:57.387
He's giving orders.

28:58.693 --> 29:01.957
- We got a lead on Rollins.
We gotta go.

29:02.001 --> 29:04.438
- I know you feel it.

29:04.481 --> 29:05.744
Nolan's still got
the department.

29:05.787 --> 29:07.746
You'll never see them,
never prove it.

29:07.789 --> 29:08.964
This is how they do it.

29:09.008 --> 29:11.793
They make you scared
of your own shadow.

29:11.837 --> 29:13.969
This is how they break you.

29:14.013 --> 29:19.105
♪

29:19.148 --> 29:21.498
- We got Rollins entering
the Wilson CTA stop

29:21.542 --> 29:23.152
two minutes
after your 10-1 call, Ruz,

29:23.196 --> 29:24.806
and then exiting again
at Belmont.

29:24.850 --> 29:27.113
- Rollins has a cousin that
lives two blocks from Belmont.

29:27.156 --> 29:28.723
Great place to hide out.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.464
- Hey, Adam.

29:30.507 --> 29:33.249
You okay?
- I'm good.

29:33.293 --> 29:36.339
- All right, we are not
relying on Patrol this time.

29:36.383 --> 29:38.124
We secure the location

29:38.167 --> 29:41.040
and contain the perimeter
ourselves, understood?

29:41.083 --> 29:43.390
Let's do it.
- Let's go.

29:47.873 --> 29:49.788
- Hey.

29:49.831 --> 29:52.312
Come on.
Let's go.

29:53.313 --> 29:56.229
[tense music]

29:56.272 --> 30:03.410
♪

30:15.248 --> 30:18.599
- Back's secure.
- Copy.

30:18.642 --> 30:20.122
- Tim Rollins, Chicago PD.
We have a warrant to enter.

30:20.166 --> 30:22.255
- I've got movement
in the house--go.

30:24.605 --> 30:27.347
- Kev, Adam,
he's heading your way.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.915
[doorknob jingles]

30:29.958 --> 30:32.526
- [panting, grunts]

30:32.569 --> 30:34.049
- Stay down!
- Stay there!

30:34.093 --> 30:36.835
Yeah, yes, stay down.

30:36.878 --> 30:38.793
- Offender in custody.

30:38.837 --> 30:40.490
- Confirm, Hailey.

30:40.534 --> 30:42.405
We got you.
We got you.

30:42.449 --> 30:43.972
- Okay.
- All right, let's go.

30:44.016 --> 30:47.193
Let's go.
Get him up, get him up.

30:47.236 --> 30:48.934
- This the gun
you shot my partner with?

30:48.977 --> 30:50.849
- Get up.
- Get him up.

30:50.892 --> 30:54.287
Let's go.

30:54.940 --> 30:56.724
- [groans]

30:59.292 --> 31:01.772
- I'm sorry, bro.

31:01.816 --> 31:04.863
- You got no reason
to be sorry.

31:04.906 --> 31:07.604
You do know I got you,
though, right?

31:07.648 --> 31:09.911
We all do.

31:09.955 --> 31:11.739
You're not alone.

31:11.782 --> 31:14.698
[somber music]

31:14.742 --> 31:21.662
♪

31:29.931 --> 31:32.716
- Yeah, I'm 10 minutes out.

31:32.760 --> 31:35.502
- Hey, if you want me,
then come get me.

31:35.545 --> 31:36.720
I could take whatever you got.

31:36.764 --> 31:38.157
- Not sure what
you're talking about.

31:38.200 --> 31:39.898
- Well, come for me,
not my unit,

31:39.941 --> 31:41.812
good cops that don't got
nothing to do with this.

31:41.856 --> 31:44.554
If I'm the one you want,
then come for me!

31:44.598 --> 31:48.384
You know I did the right thing!

31:48.428 --> 31:50.604
- "The right thing"?

31:50.647 --> 31:53.259
Is that what you think you did?

31:53.302 --> 31:55.826
You're the hero
who crumpled the Blue Wall?

31:55.870 --> 31:58.525
- Doyle was a gladiator cop
that killed--

31:58.568 --> 32:00.701
- Doyle was a dead man!

32:00.744 --> 32:05.184
He was already killed,
and then you killed him again.

32:05.227 --> 32:07.534
You left his children
with a dead father

32:07.577 --> 32:10.667
they gotta be ashamed of,
and for what?

32:10.711 --> 32:13.670
You're standing
exactly where you were.

32:13.714 --> 32:18.414
Blue Wall's
still all around you.

32:18.458 --> 32:21.940
I'm gonna keep coming for you

32:21.983 --> 32:25.247
in any way I want

32:25.291 --> 32:28.729
until I have your badge.

32:28.772 --> 32:34.865
♪

32:38.957 --> 32:39.783
.

32:39.827 --> 32:41.611
- Evening.

32:41.655 --> 32:44.266
Heard you closed the case.

32:44.310 --> 32:46.747
Congrats.

32:46.790 --> 32:48.357
- Really?

32:48.401 --> 32:51.970
- It's professional courtesy.

32:52.013 --> 32:54.407
All right, I read it
in the management book.

32:54.450 --> 32:57.845
It's supposed to build trust.

32:57.888 --> 33:00.456
Do you like me now?

33:00.500 --> 33:03.416
- Look, I know you didn't get
me 48 and protection for free.

33:03.459 --> 33:04.634
Can we just cut to the part

33:04.678 --> 33:05.809
where you tell me
what you want?

33:05.853 --> 33:08.769
- I gave you 48
because you were right.

33:08.812 --> 33:10.292
Look, I get it.

33:10.336 --> 33:12.686
You look at me, and you see
everyone that came before me:

33:12.729 --> 33:14.731
Kelton, Woods, Brennan.

33:14.775 --> 33:17.386
You know their file
is still up at Ivory?

33:17.430 --> 33:19.910
They hated you.
- They didn't hide it.

33:19.954 --> 33:22.043
- I'm not them.
- They all said that too.

33:22.087 --> 33:25.699
- I'm sure they did,
but I'm just here to do a job,

33:25.742 --> 33:28.006
a job that I am very good at.

33:31.531 --> 33:34.012
I'm something new, Hank.

33:34.055 --> 33:36.188
- Part of the new world, huh?

33:36.231 --> 33:38.799
- Yeah.

33:38.842 --> 33:42.063
- Chicago's an old city, Sam.

33:42.107 --> 33:44.544
- It is.

33:44.587 --> 33:46.546
[phone buzzes]

33:46.589 --> 33:49.723
You should get that.
Go ahead.

33:49.766 --> 33:52.682
Today was fun.

33:52.726 --> 33:54.902
The fight's
always the good part.

33:54.945 --> 33:57.078
It's the only way
you really see people.

33:57.122 --> 34:00.081
- Hmm.

34:02.518 --> 34:05.043
Voight.

34:22.103 --> 34:25.150
It's starting to get cold.

34:31.286 --> 34:34.333
- Yeah, I know
I got two options.

34:36.726 --> 34:41.731
Let you make some deal for me,
or I hand over my badge.

34:41.775 --> 34:43.994
- Well, I can't have you
in my unit, Kev.

34:44.038 --> 34:45.170
Not if--
- I know.

34:45.213 --> 34:47.346
Not if I'm jeopardizing cases.

34:47.389 --> 34:50.262
Or I'm risking team's lives.
I get it.

34:50.305 --> 34:53.265
- So let me help you.

34:56.137 --> 34:59.793
I already talked to Nolan.
Listen.

35:04.885 --> 35:07.453
The deal would be
I put a beef on your record.

35:07.496 --> 35:08.932
Official complaint.

35:08.976 --> 35:13.111
I mean, it would tie you down.

35:13.154 --> 35:14.590
It means
you'd never make detective,

35:14.634 --> 35:18.725
never leave my unit.

35:18.768 --> 35:21.815
It's a brick,

35:21.858 --> 35:24.034
but Nolan would stop coming--

35:24.078 --> 35:25.384
- I'm not taking that.

35:25.427 --> 35:27.255
- Then you're not
gonna be a cop anymore.

35:27.299 --> 35:30.780
- Maybe I don't wanna
be a cop anymore.

35:30.824 --> 35:33.479
I'm constantly
looking over my shoulder.

35:33.522 --> 35:35.133
I'm mad

35:35.176 --> 35:37.178
every hour,
every minute, every second.

35:37.222 --> 35:40.660
I'm mad at Nolan, I'm mad
at you, I'm mad at Ruzek.

35:40.703 --> 35:42.488
I'm mad at every white cop

35:42.531 --> 35:46.100
that feels like
they can make a deal for me.

35:46.144 --> 35:48.668
And every cop that's done
this job the wrong way,

35:48.711 --> 35:52.193
which means I'm mad at myself.

35:52.237 --> 35:53.412
I'm so mad, I don't even think

35:53.455 --> 35:54.978
I can do the job
the right way anymore.

35:55.022 --> 35:57.807
- Then do it different.

35:57.851 --> 35:59.200
- [scoffs]
- Do it different.

35:59.244 --> 36:01.289
That's the win.
You get to do it different.

36:01.333 --> 36:03.291
- And Nolan skates?
- Nolan.

36:03.335 --> 36:07.643
Nolan, the way he polices, he's
not gonna last another year.

36:07.687 --> 36:09.689
- Then what's the point
of giving him a damn thing?

36:09.732 --> 36:12.474
- Because it's not
a new world yet.

36:12.518 --> 36:13.997
It's just not.

36:14.041 --> 36:15.956
- So we just wait
for the whole world to change

36:15.999 --> 36:19.307
and just pull me up?

36:22.397 --> 36:25.226
What would you do?

36:25.270 --> 36:28.316
Voight?

36:28.360 --> 36:32.320
In my skin, with this world,
would you do that?

36:32.364 --> 36:34.540
- Me?

36:34.583 --> 36:37.369
No.

36:41.286 --> 36:44.680
I'd say you are a good cop.

36:44.724 --> 36:47.770
And you're a good man, Kevin.

36:47.814 --> 36:50.947
And you ask me, as soon as
you're not one anymore,

36:50.991 --> 36:53.994
they're winning.

36:54.037 --> 36:56.953
[somber music]

36:56.997 --> 36:59.391
♪

36:59.434 --> 37:03.090
Kevin, I...

37:03.133 --> 37:06.093
Listen, I'll back you
no matter what you choose.

37:09.183 --> 37:12.055
But the question is,
what do you wanna do?

37:12.099 --> 37:19.237
♪

37:33.163 --> 37:35.253
[door unlocks]

37:37.603 --> 37:40.258
[door shuts, locks]

37:45.828 --> 37:48.266
- Nobody's home.
I already checked.

37:48.309 --> 37:50.703
I wouldn't wanna
scare your family.

37:50.746 --> 37:52.357
- What the hell
do you think you're doing?

37:52.400 --> 37:56.839
- I'm a cop too.
Nobody saw me come in.

37:56.883 --> 37:59.538
- [chuckles]

38:02.149 --> 38:04.543
You're gonna kill me?
- No.

38:09.417 --> 38:11.941
I'm gonna tell you our way out.

38:11.985 --> 38:13.421
- Well, that's
not how this works.

38:13.465 --> 38:17.512
- It is
if I take the third option...

38:17.556 --> 38:20.341
where I give up my badge
a different way.

38:20.385 --> 38:21.647
- [scoffs]

38:21.690 --> 38:24.432
- Where I sue you

38:24.476 --> 38:28.262
and I sue the Chicago
Police Department...

38:28.306 --> 38:32.440
where I detail the harassment,
the intimidation,

38:32.484 --> 38:35.138
the kilo of dope
you planted in my car,

38:35.182 --> 38:36.966
the officers
who pulled me over,

38:37.010 --> 38:38.794
the break-in at my house,

38:38.838 --> 38:41.406
the beatdown.

38:41.449 --> 38:44.539
The innocent cop
you let get shot,

38:44.583 --> 38:47.455
the fact that you ordered other
officers to do your bidding--

38:47.499 --> 38:49.414
- You might need
some sort of evidence.

38:49.457 --> 38:52.330
- Yeah.

38:52.373 --> 38:53.983
But do you really think
all those men

38:54.027 --> 38:57.987
are gonna stand by you?

38:58.031 --> 39:01.295
When I rip you limb from limb
in front of the media?

39:01.339 --> 39:04.646
When I give up my badge,
my job, and my life

39:04.690 --> 39:07.519
to stand on the podium
and call you a racist?

39:10.217 --> 39:12.785
When every member of my team
backs me?

39:12.828 --> 39:17.398
When I march in the streets
with your face on my poster?

39:17.442 --> 39:20.314
When I come for your job,
your pension,

39:20.358 --> 39:22.838
your house, your name?

39:22.882 --> 39:25.188
All while you're still living?

39:25.232 --> 39:28.496
While your three sons watch?

39:28.540 --> 39:31.891
I don't wanna give up this job,

39:31.934 --> 39:34.067
but if you keep
coming after me,

39:34.110 --> 39:37.113
any member of my unit,
or any other cop,

39:37.157 --> 39:39.681
I promise you

39:39.725 --> 39:42.510
I will give it all away.

39:42.554 --> 39:46.949
I will make it my job
to come after you.

39:46.993 --> 39:49.038
And I will destroy you.

39:49.082 --> 39:52.041
[tense music]

39:52.085 --> 39:59.266
♪

40:25.945 --> 40:29.383
[exhales]

40:29.427 --> 40:31.646
- Pass the ball, bro.
Pass it.

40:42.875 --> 40:45.791
[solemn music]

40:45.834 --> 40:52.798
♪

41:15.516 --> 41:15.734
.

41:15.777 --> 41:18.693
[tense music]

41:18.737 --> 41:25.657
♪

41:44.371 --> 41:47.505
[wolf howls]
